- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes algorithms for computing the minimum spanning trees. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and optimization problems. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with optimization problems and finding minimum cost spanning trees. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with geometric graphs and monotonicity properties.
